additional_context.raw_instruction: deploy to AWS with containers and a Postgres DB

suggestions.architecture: single service app with managed database

network_settings.egress: allow all to 0.0.0.0/0 via NAT for package updates and external APIs

infrastructure.summary: Deploy app container on AWS ECS Fargate with an Application Load Balancer; use Amazon RDS for PostgreSQL; store secrets in AWS Secrets Manager; images in ECR; networking via VPC with public ALB and private service subnets; CI/CD via GitHub Actions to ECR/ECS.

autoscaling.policy: scale on CPU > 60% or ALB request count

database.networking: deployed in private subnets, no public access
database.connectivity: ECS tasks via security group allow 5432

observability.logs: CloudWatch Logs (ECS task log group with retention 30 days)
observability.metrics: CloudWatch metrics and ALB target metrics

steps: Create VPC with 2 public and 2 private subnets across 2 AZs; add NAT gateway for private subnets.
Create RDS PostgreSQL instance in private subnets; create security groups (RDS allow 5432 from ECS tasks).
Create ACM certificate for your domain in same region; set up Route 53 hosted zone if needed.
Author Dockerfile and .dockerignore; build and push image to ECR.
Create ECS task definition with CPU/Mem, container port 8080, environment vars, and Secrets Manager refs; enable CloudWatch Logs.
Create ALB in public subnets with HTTPS listener, target group to ECS service; security group allows 443 from internet and 8080 from ALB to tasks.
Create ECS service using Fargate in private subnets, attach to target group; desired count 1; enable auto-scaling.
Configure GitHub Actions with OIDC to assume an AWS role; add workflow to build/push image and deploy updated task definition.
Set DNS record (A/AAAA alias) in Route 53 to ALB; verify health checks and app availability.
Migrate/seed database using a one-off ECS task.
infrastructure.compose_migration_note: Codebase lacks Dockerfile/Compose; create Dockerfile first. You can still define a docker-compose.yml for local dev; for AWS use ECS directly (no Compose) or use aws/ecs-cli compose conversion if desired.
